div.span: The application first checks for cache for the requested data. If it finds the data (a "cache hit"), it returns it quickly. If the data is not found ("cache miss"), the application fetches the data from the database instead, which is a slower process.
The application may update the cache with the data from the database, so that we will get a "cache hit" the next time.
